 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
Katerra scaled and vertically integrated too much before it had a product t=
hat customers actually wanted to buy. They hadn&#8217;t figured out how to =
make prefab competitive with stick-built construction, which meant that the=
re wasn&#8217;t enough demand for the &#8220;distribution&#8221; products t=
o sell the actual products, the materials. It also meant that the company, =
though &#8220;pre-Product Market Fit,&#8221; was too large and unwieldy to =
iterate quickly to the right products and economics. &#8220;Ideally, early =
stage product development involves rapid iteration and prototyping, to figu=
re out what needs to be built as quickly as possible,&#8221; Potter writes.=
 &#8220;But the pace of product development at Katerra always felt sluggish=
=2E&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Here is one big lesson from Kater=
ra: </span><strong>don&#8217;t vertically integrate too much, too early</st=
rong><span>.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>When I said that Kater=
ra </span><em>almost </em><span>perfectly fit the definition of a vertical =
integrator, this is one of the things I was referring to. The third of five=
 bullets in the definition is &#8220;Modularize commoditized components whi=
le controlling overall system integration.&#8221;&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">It seems as if Katerra tried to integrate commoditized components=
 in an attempt to drive down their costs and make a margin on producing and=
 selling them at volume. Which would make sense if the costs of those mater=
ials were the big bottleneck in home construction, but materials costs aren=
&#8217;t the biggest bottleneck in home construction. High materials costs =
may increase the cost of construction, but they don&#8217;t typically preve=
nt homes from being built, and savings from cheaper materials can be overwh=
elmed by increases in logistics or labor costs.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
<span>So a second lesson: </span><strong>focus on the bottleneck</strong><s=
pan>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Attempting to integrate relatively =
commoditized components comes with another disadvantage. One of the benefit=
s of being a Vertical Integrator is that you can ride advances in certain i=
nputs without locking yourself into any but the most critical to your syste=
m. Recall that </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/9c7f9cec-84d=
b-47fd-85b7-e105b3d16092?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKb=
qOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: und=
erline;">Base Power Company</a><span> &#8220;assembles and will soon manufa=
cture battery packs itself, but it doesn&#8217;t make battery cells&#8230; =
Base believes that cells will be commoditized, and that </span><strong>pack=
 assembly allows it to benefit from that commoditization and potentially in=
tegrate new cell types as better chemistries emerge</strong><span>.&#8221;&=
#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Katerra, on the other hand, locked itself=
 into certain materials. One that Potter calls out specifically is cross-la=
minated timber, or CLT, a &#8220;super plywood.&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D=
"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;"><span>&#8220;Green technologies are enhancing our ability to create =
more sustainable solutions that also meet structural and aesthetic demands,=
&#8221; Nick Milestone, Katerra's director of mass timber, </span><a href=
