 0 20px 0;">As a developer and landowner, it will be able to offtake its ow=
n supply from the MMFs, and capture even more of the margin in the process.=
 Because housing is so large and fragmented across so many markets, it can =
do this without threatening its relationships with its developer customers,=
 which is often a risk of backwards integration.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color=
: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"=
><span>In </span><strong>Phase III of the Master Plan</strong><span>, Cuby =
might go direct, and enter the consumer market with their homes directly, l=
ike Tesla does with cars. It could create a seamless experience from the fi=
rst step: pick a plot of land, tell Cuby exactly what kind of home you want=
, and move in within 30 days.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55=
, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Cuby might =
also offer financing, maintenance, and other services to homeowners, includ=
ing, one might imagine, the ability to easily alter or upgrade your home as=
 your needs and preferences change.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Much of this=
 has been tried before. Katerra vertically integrated the supply chain. Lev=
ittown sold direct to consumer. Sears built a damn good Kit Home until the =
economy crashed in the Great Depression and the company was no longer able =
to support the financing it had extended to its now-underwater customers.&#=
160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The trick is sequencing it right: building a fact=
ory that can build homes cheaper and faster, with less skilled labor. Then =
scaling. Then adding. All with an eye towards driving down costs, deliverin=
g a better product, and filling unmet demand.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Ti=
ming matters, too, and Cuby&#8217;s feels right.&#160;&#160;</p><p style=3D=
"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;">Building more housing is a bipartisan issue, and any company that ca=
n do that faster and cheaper while maintaining quality will have a lot of i=
nterest from city, state, and federal governments. Housing, Your Washington=
 Office told me, makes Hero Mayors. America wants to build again, and housi=
ng may be the next manufacturing.&#160;</p><div class=3D"captioned-image-co=
